abstract: Lorenzo Bouier missed his singlegame school record by three yards as he rushed for 205 yards and two touchdowns yesterday to lead Maine to a 17-8 victory over the U.S. Merchant Marine Academy at Tomb Memorial Field in Kings Point, L.I.

abstract: SOUTH BEND, Ind., Sept. 6-- Forced to play without its all-America quarterback, Mark Herrmann, for the first time since he entered college in 1977, Purdue was no match for Notre Dame today, and the Irish opened their 94th football season by beating the Boilermakers, 31-10.
headline_main: Irish Top Purdue; Irish Rout Purdue in Season Opener, 31-10 Passes to Hunter Click Purdue Retaliates Briefly

abstract: He knows a little about physics and a lot about football, so the Jets' coach, Walt Michaels, asks: "What's that law of physics? Bodies in motion tend to get hurt?"

abstract: THE stereotype pop-music record executive sometimes re  calls a debased version of Diogenes. Except that instead of searching for an honest man, the record executive is searching for a trend--any trend, as long as it will sell.

abstract: Senator Donald W. Stewart of Alabama, elected two years ago to complete the term of the late Senator James B. Allen, was forced into a Democratic runoff in Tuesday's primary election. Jeremiah Denton, a former Vietnam war prisoner, won the Republican nomination.
